**Once upon a time there was a young wizard, slender and elegant in his appearance and attire. He wore a white tunic, embroidered with golden threads, that shone in the sun and enhanced his beauty. The black cloak that covered his shoulders was made of soft and smooth fabric, with a hood that gave him a mysterious air. His long and dark hair, tied in a thin braid, was a work of art in itself, with loose strands falling over his shoulders. Together with his pale and smooth skin, and his intense and deep eyes, of a greenish tone, he conveyed an aura of wisdom and intelligence. In his right hand, he held a staff, made of dark and rough wood, that had been carved with his own hands. The rustic appearance of the staff contrasted with the elegance of his appearance and attire, but at the same time complemented his mysterious and enigmatic air. His staff was an extension of his magic and power, and he used it with confidence and skill. His confident and proud posture further complemented his majestic appearance.** - Variations by <@285251809042235394> (fast)
